# Spring Boot Application Rules

## Project Structure

Use a layered layout under `src/main/java/<base-package>/`:

- `controller/` — REST endpoints; no business logic
- `service/` — business logic and orchestration
- `repository/` — data access (Spring Data JPA interfaces)
- `model/` or `entity/` — JPA entities and domain types
- `dto/` — request/response objects; never expose entities directly
- `config/` — `@Configuration` classes, security, beans
- `exception/` — custom exceptions and `@ControllerAdvice` handlers

Keep `Application.java` in the base package only.

## Dependencies & Build

- Prefer **Spring Boot 3.x** with **Java 17+**
- **Pipeline / CI:** this template is **Maven-only** — use `pom.xml`, `./mvnw`, and merge [.docs/maven-profiles.example.xml](../../.docs/maven-profiles.example.xml) per [TESTING.md](../../.docs/TESTING.md). Commands come from `project-config.yml` → `build.*`
- **Non-pipeline projects:** Gradle (`build.gradle.kts`) is fine if the repo already uses it — match the existing build tool
- Core starters: `spring-boot-starter-web`, `spring-boot-starter-data-jpa`, `spring-boot-starter-validation`
- Test starter: `spring-boot-starter-test` with JUnit 5
- Run locally (Maven): `./mvnw spring-boot:run` — or `./gradlew bootRun` for Gradle-only repos
- Package (Maven): `./mvnw package` — or `./gradlew build` for Gradle-only repos

## Coding Conventions

```java
// ✅ Controller — thin, validates input, delegates to service
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/users")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class UserController {
    private final UserService userService;

    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public UserResponse getUser(@PathVariable Long id) {
        return userService.findById(id);
    }
}

// ❌ BAD — business logic in controller
// ❌ BAD — returning JPA entity directly
```

- Use constructor injection (`@RequiredArgsConstructor` or explicit constructor); avoid `@Autowired` on fields
- Validate request bodies with `@Valid` and Jakarta Bean Validation annotations
- Map entities ↔ DTOs in the service layer (or a dedicated mapper)
- Use `@Transactional` on service methods that write to the database
- Handle errors with `@ControllerAdvice` + `@ExceptionHandler`; return consistent error responses

## Configuration

- Externalize config in `application.yml` (preferred) or `application.properties`
- Use profiles: `application-dev.yml`, `application-prod.yml`
- Never commit secrets; use environment variables or a secrets manager
- Enable `spring.jpa.open-in-view=false` for REST APIs

## Testing

- Unit test services with Mockito (`@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)`)
- Integration test controllers with `@WebMvcTest` or full context with `@SpringBootTest`
- Use `@DataJpaTest` for repository layer tests
- Name tests descriptively: `shouldReturnUser_whenIdExists()`

## REST API

- Use plural nouns: `/api/users`, not `/api/user`
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes (201 for create, 204 for delete)
- Version APIs when needed: `/api/v1/users`
- Document with Springdoc OpenAPI (`springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui`) when the project uses it
